CEZ Solar Deals Investigated by Czech Finance Ministry, HN Says

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-06-07T06:22:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/cez-solar-deals-investigated-by-czech-finance-ministry-hn-says.html
The Czech  Finance Ministry  is
investigating  CEZ AS (CEZ) ’s contracts for its solar plants,
 Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing unidentified people familiar
with the matter.  CEZ paid more than 2 billion koruna ($120 million) to its
main supplier Amun.Re, a company with an unclear ownership, for
an order from CE Solar that was worth about 1.1 billion koruna,
the newspaper said, citing related documents it obtained without
identifying its source.  The Finance Ministry’s spokesman, Jakub Haas, declined to
comment, the newspaper reported.  The Finance Ministry’s press department was unavailable for
comment when called by Bloomberg News and no press officer at
CEZ was immediately available for comment today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  